label: time_select
text: SphinctoMeter Biofeed 6. Finally Press the COUGH REFLEX Key and ask the Patient to COUGH a YELLOW GRAPH with Values will appear 5. The device also calculates the AVERAGE SQUEEZE pressure over 10 secs ��4. Ask the Patient to contract the Sphincter muscle to a maximum of 10 secs and then Press the SQUEEZE key a RED GRAPH with values will appea 3. The next measure SQUEEZE PRESSURE will be chosen automatically. 2. Press the REST key a Green graph showing the RESTING pressure values will appear. 1. To determine the RESTING PRESSURE wait for 10 seconds after inserting the SENSOR. STEPS for the TEST 5. User can only skip the Repeat SQUEEZE and COUGH modes 4. Once the Test is started User has to go through the REST SQUEEZE and COUGH ANAL REFLEX modes 3. User can also Repeat modes ( SQUEEZE and COUGH) 2. User can Select the Time for each Test 1. The test will go through various modes like REST SQUEEZE and COUGH ANAL REFLEX TO PERFORM A TEST 160 150 Cough Reflex mm Hg 150 100 Squeeze mm Hg 60 40 - 60 Reating mm Hg Males Females Sphincter Pressure Normal Range of Sphincter Pressure Values • COUGH ANAL REFLEX - to ascertain the Anal Contraction during a Cough • AVERAGE SQUEEZE - Endurance of Squeeze average after 10 secs of Squeeze • SQUEEZE - maximum force applied during the test • RESTING - applied by the un-contracted muscle The SPHINCTER PRESSURE values of interest are INSTRUCTIONS TO USE
